\loch\af2\dbch\af2\hich\f2\strike0\ulnone\cf2 Roles in Action on Two Bills}{\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s0\fi0\sb200\sa0\aspalpha\aspnum\adjustright\ltrpar\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\qj\faauto\sl260\slmult0\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24{\rtlch\af2\alang1025\afs24
\ltrch\b0\i0\fs20\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\loch\af2\dbch\af2\hich\f2\strike0\ulnone\cf2 The Justice's activities were so considerable, in fact, that he was called upon to consider the constitutionality of two laws, the Lever Food Control Bill and the Army Appropriations Act, that he had helped either draft or administer. In neither case, Professor Murphy relates, did he disqualify - or, in judicial terms, ''recuse'' - himself, as the circumstances seemed to require. Instead, he simply refused to sign the court's opinion and concurred only in its re sult.}
{\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s0\fi0\sb200\sa0\aspalpha\aspnum\adjustright\ltrpar\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\qj\faauto\sl260\slmult0\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24{\rtlch\af2\alang1025\afs24\ltrch\b0\i0\fs20\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033
\loch\af2\dbch\af2\hich\f2\strike0\ulnone\cf2 ''Perhaps,'' Professor Murphy wrote, ''where his private political involvement with aspects of the case was not known to the public Brandeis felt no need to disqualify himself, but nonetheless did feel the need to satisfy personal ethical qualms by taking only a very minimal role in the ultimate judicial decision.''}
{\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s0\fi0\sb200\sa0\aspalpha\aspnum\adjustright\ltrpar\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\qj\faauto\sl260\slmult0\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24{\rtlch\af2\alang1025\afs24\ltrch\b0\i0\fs20\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033
\loch\af2\dbch\af2\hich\f2\strike0\ulnone\cf2 Through such activities, along with his ongoing but less conspicuous leadership of the American Zionist movement, ''Brandeis changed the norms of extrajudicial conduct,'' Professor Murphy wrote, adding, ''His incredibly open and extensive political behavior made it possible for members of the Court to establish intimate advisory relationships with later administrations.''}
{\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s0\fi0\sb200\sa0\aspalpha\aspnum\adjustright\ltrpar\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\qj\faauto\sl260\slmult0\rtlch\afs24\ltrch\fs24{\rtlch\af2\alang1025\afs24\ltrch\b0\i0\fs20\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033
